===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

[[File:A lindworm.jpg|thumb]]

# {{lb|en|mythology}} A lindworm is a slithering wingless type of "dragon" with scaled skin, a long serpentine body like in Chinese dragons, two clawed arms in the upper body and a dragon-like head. May have either a poisonous or fiery breath. This type of dragon is especially found in Norse mythology.<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%9E%C3%B3ra_Borgarhj%C7%ABrtr#Thora_in_the_sagas</ref><ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fafnir</ref>
# {{lb|en|folklore, fairy tales and heraldry}} A vague draconic creature, especially in heraldry; can look the same as the creature from the first definition above or it can be just as anything a dragon can be depicted, mainly found in folklore, fairy tales and heraldry of Germany, Scandinavia and England.

